text: A brother here recently talked about how Indo-European religion was based on the idea of "friendship with the gods" and pagan man was certain of the deity being his personal friend, reminded me how St. Porphyrios said Christ is our friend and wants us to also see Him as such.

Sort of like how some more old school guys go like oh I know a car repair guy in that town he'll take care of it or oh the bouncer at this club is my buddy he has my back if I get drunk and something happens etc. but it's literally with God instead. St. Porphyrios talks about it.
He was talking about the deep north not the Greeks as we know them maybe I should have made it more clear though...
There are moments during service when one is supposed to kneel, bow down, touch the ground, etc. too
